# STS2 Dwell Targeting ÔÇö AI health + test workflow

Chase does not read telemetry. **The agent** uses these sources to understand live mod state and catch regressions.

## Chase reports bugs (no screenshots required)

When something is broken, Chase stays on that screen and says a short phrase, e.g.:

- **"campfire broken"** / **"smith broken"** / **"upgrade screen broken"**

The agent reads (in order):

1. `%APPDATA%\SlayTheSpire2\logs\dwell-targeting-health.json` ÔÇö if `updatedUtc` is within **60 seconds**
2. Log tail from `logPath` in that JSON

Do **not** ask Chase to screenshot unless health JSON is stale or missing.

## While the game is running (always-on)

Every ~3 seconds the mod writes:

`%APPDATA%\SlayTheSpire2\logs\dwell-targeting-health.json`

**When working on this mod** (overlay bugs, FPS, missing targets, scan lifecycle), read this file first if `updatedUtc` is within the last **60 seconds** ÔÇö that means STS2 is likely running with the mod loaded.

Interpret key fields:

| Field | Healthy static screen | Problem signal |
|-------|----------------------|----------------|
| `findAllCallsPerFrame` | ~0 | Ôëą 0.5 Ôćĺ rescan storm (tree walk every frame) |
| `nodesVisitedPerFrame` | low / 0 | very high Ôćĺ FPS killer |
| `overlayMode` | matches screen | Room on smith grid Ôćĺ mode detection bug |
| `targets.pileCards` | > 0 on upgrade grid | 0 Ôćĺ cards not scanned |
| `targets.roomButtons` | > 0 on campfire | 0 Ôćĺ Rest/Smith scan stuck |
| `targets.hasBack` | true on sub-screens | false Ôćĺ back overlay missing |
| `targets.hasViewUpgrades` | true on smith grid | false Ôćĺ toggle not found |
| `targets.confirmOnly` | true only after card picked | true on fresh grid Ôćĺ confirm suppression bug |
| `alerts` | `[]` | non-empty Ôćĺ read and act on each string |
| `screenHint` | human-readable expectation | compare to `targets` |

Also skim the log tail (`logPath` in JSON) for `[WARN]`, `[Mode]`, `[Pile]`, `[Room]`, and repeated snapshot lines.

## Before changing scan-state code (offline)

Run **before** install when editing:

- `ScreenEntryScanState.cs`, `ScanRuntime.cs`, `ScreenScanTiming.cs`
- Overlays using `_entryScan` (Room, Map, Shop, Event, CharacterSelect)

```powershell
dotnet test tests/DwellTargeting.Tests.csproj
```

All tests must pass. If red, fix before `install.ps1`.

## After code changes

1. `dotnet test` (if scan-state touched)
2. `dotnet build` + `install.ps1`
3. Ask Chase to restart STS2 if DLL changed
4. Re-read `dwell-targeting-health.json` after they reproduce the screen

## Two tools, two jobs

| Tool | Runs when | Catches |
|------|-----------|---------|
| `dotnet test` | Agent, before install | Logic bugs (retry-forever, give-up doesn't quiet) |
| `dwell-targeting-health.json` | Game running | Live FPS storms, zero targets, wrong mode, per-overlay gaps |

Do not ask Chase to run either unless the game or test command failed on the agent side.
